MONTILLA FROM SPAIN

South of Cordoba, some of the most un- usual fortified wines of Spain are pro- duced. The word ‘amontillado’ comes from this town. From Alvear, there is a mag- nificent light, pale aperitif which should be served chilled. And they also send us the precious and rare 1750 Solera—a true collector’s item.

Montilla Fina... 2.19 24.50 Dry, pale, crisp. Montilla 1750 Solera ....... 9.95 110.00

Here is a precious Solera that traces its origin to a cask that was laid down in 1750 and has been replenished regularly since. The average age approximates 100 years. Medium dry, rich in flavor, extraor- dinary bouquet, intriguing. From Alvear.
